This paper deals with the issue of maintaining the historical integrity of shared resources in social media, which involves analyzing the features of posts and linked resources to model user intention. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories, including social media analysis (cs.SI), cyber-physical systems (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), software development (cs.SD), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). However, given the focus on social media and user intention, cs.SI is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CY and cs.IR.
